Consumed by LÖVE's love.sound (Ogg Vorbis decode) and love.video — the Ogg
container/framing layer libvorbis (and, upstream, libtheora) sit on. First of
the audio-vendoring trio (libogg → libvorbis → libmodplug). Plain C, no
exceptions, no setjmp — links cleanly into the EH artifact as neutral objects.

Files:
  include/ogg/ogg.h, os_types.h   verbatim upstream.
  include/ogg/config_types.h      OURS — generated from the upstream
                                  config_types.h.in for wasm32-wasi (the
                                  stdint path: ogg_int16/32/64_t -> intN_t).
                                  This is the build product configure/cmake
                                  emits; the .in template is not vendored.
  src/framing.c, bitwise.c        verbatim upstream (the whole library).
  src/crctable.h                  verbatim upstream (committed CRC table,
                                  #included by framing.c). src/config.h is NOT
                                  vendored: framing.c only includes it under
                                  HAVE_CONFIG_H, which this build never defines.

Built to a static archive by build.sh; witnessed by run.sh (a page/packet
framing round-trip — data + b_o_s/e_o_s survive) under node + Chromium +
wasmtime. Update by re-dropping from a newer release and refreshing this PIN
(regenerate config_types.h if the .in template changes). Never edit upstream
files in place.
